annotation.text: Each of the timers will execute, but at different times. I would expect the UI task to be generated 6 times, once for each timer/path. What you observe due to the XOR gateways, however, is that only one path is executed while the rest are frozen at the gateways. A better approach might be to halt the flows of the other timers once one has executed, or to use a Complex node that specifies how many paths it expects to arrive before executing.

While this process reaches each End Event node along a path, the process does not appear to ever complete. You can see this by checking the process instances in /designer - PMX_LargeProcess never passes the Active arrow to the Completed checkmark. Can you determine why this might be the case?
